{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We don't want it cut, because you lose a certain amount of bread whenever you cut it, you see.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So we want a piece for three.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And then if we didn't eat it, because we had stored some, we could give it back next day, and say, I want a piece for six.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we'd give back the three piece, and we might have shaved off half a millimeter of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And-- it-- it was, yeah, Rudy was an entrepreneur and a scavenger, and he was an ideal man to have on your side.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I think another there, I ought to say it this time, is that I probably owe-- maybe my life, even-- a lot to Rudy.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Not only in remembering everything, but also in-- in pulling me through during my time in-- in Belsen and afterwards.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I've found since that many survivors have survived in pairs and in couples and in-- in groups.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Very few people have survived entirely on their own.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Most people have had somebody else that they egged each other on, if you like, in a way to survive, and not to give up, and to carry on and-- and do things, and work together and help each other.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "There were many people like that, which I could cite, but Frank-- Anne Frank--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that time in Belsen, I don't think he would, because I didn't have to work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and really there wasn't anything else, except the food and the appel-- he couldn't help me with the appel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We all had to stand there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he-- he was punished several times because people complained about what he was doing-- giving them all the water, and all that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was punished several times, and there was solitary confinement.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
